32013\n| clubs3 = [[Rah Ahan F.C.|Rah Ahan]]\n| caps3 = 46\n| goals3 = 14\n| years4 = 2013\u2013\n| clubs4 = [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]]\n| caps4 = 111 <!-- \u0641\u0642\u0637 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u0646\u062c\u0627\u0645 \u0634\u062f\u0647 \u062f\u0631 \u0644\u06cc\u06af -->\n| goals4 = 13\n| years5 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs5 = \u2192 [[Tractor S.C.|Tractor]] (loan)\n| caps5 = 6\n| goals5 = 2\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\n| nationalyears2 = 2009\u20132010\n| nationalyears3 = 2013\n| nationalyears4 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Iran national under-17 football team|Iran U17]]\n| nationalteam2 = [[Iran national under-20 football team|Iran U20]]\n| nationalteam3 = [[Iran national under-23 football team|Iran U22]]\n| nationalteam4 = [[Iran national football team|Iran]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 4\n| nationalcaps2 = 5\n| nationalcaps3 = 3\n| nationalcaps4 = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalgoals3 = 1\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 24 November 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 3 September 2015\n}}\n\n'''Omid Alishah''' ({{lang-fa|\u0627\u0645\u06cc\u062f \u0639\u0627\u0644\u06cc\u0634\u0627\u0647}}<nowiki/>l born January 10, 1992) is an [[Iran]]ian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] club [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] and the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].\n\nHe signed a two-year contract with [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] on 11 June 2013 and made his debut on 16 August 2013. On 23 November 2014, Alishah scored the winning goal in the [[Tehran derby]] against rival [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] in the 78th minute. has also played for [[F.C. Nassaji Mazandaran|Nassaji Mazandaran]], [[Naft Tehran F.C.|Naft Tehran]], [[Rah Ahan Tehran F.C.|Rah Ahan]] and [[Tractor S.C.|Tractor]]. Also, He was the [[2015\u201316 Persian Gulf Pro League|2015\u201316 PGPL Top Goal Assistant]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Nassaji===\n\nAlishah started his career at [[Nassaji Mazandaran F.C.|Nassaji]] while he was 17.<ref>[http://www.persianleague.com/teams.html?sid=20&view=player&id=1589 Persianleague.com]</ref> He debuted for the club on January 7, 2010 against [[Shirin Faraz F.C.|Shirin Faraz]] when he was chosen as a starter by the coach [[Nader Dastneshan]].<ref>[http://www.abrarnews.com/sport/1388/881019/html/page11.htm#s541653 Abrarnews.com]</ref>\n\n===Naft Tehran===\n\nIn 2010\u201311 season, Alishah joined newly promoted IPL team [[Naft Tehran F.C.|Naft Tehran]].<ref>[http://www.goal.com/iran/news/1825/%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/2010/07/21/2034628/%DA%AF%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B4-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%84-%DA%AF%D9%84-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D9%86%D9%82%D9%84-%D9%88-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AA%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%84%D9%8A%DA%AF-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%B1 Goal.com]</ref> During his time at Naft, he failed to make any appearances for the first team. He was also a part of [[Naft Tehran F.C.|Naft Tehran U-21]] and won the [[Tehran Football Competitions|2010\u201311 Tehran U\u201321 League]].<ref>[http://www.footballtehran.com/id/269 Footballtehran.com]</ref><ref>[http://www.nioc.ir/portal/Home/ShowPage.aspx?Object=NEWS&ID=12205543-7203-4f4a-9ce3-acef196cbbdb&LayoutID=d56819c3-861b-4f26-a4af-36684d521883&CategoryID=40295507-1e70-49ec-af82-e5eeba6870bc Nioc.ir]</ref>\n\n===Rah Ahan===\nAfter a season at Naft, Alishah was signed up by [[Ali Daei]] for [[Rah Ahan F.C.|Rah Ahan]].<ref>[http://www.asriran.com/fa/news/175100/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C%DA%A9%D9%86-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%85-%D8%AC%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87-%D8%A2%D9%87%D9%86-%D9%BE%DB%8C%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%AA Asriran.com]</ref> Ali Daei moved him up the field and into a more attacking position using Alishah as a right winger/second striker instead of right back where he had been used by his previous managers. Alishah with his blistering pace quickly managed to find his way into the starting line-up scoring 5 goals in his first nine games. He had a less successful second half of a season mainly due to a [[Cruciate ligament]] injury in a match against [[S.C. Damash|Damash Gilan]] in March 2012.<ref>[http://www.mashreghnews.ir/fa/news/107331/%D9%BE%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%85-%D8%AF%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C-%D9%84%DB%8C%DA%AF-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF Mashreghnews.ir]</ref> He had been far from the team till December 2012.<ref>[http://sorinetsport.ir/Default.aspx?cat=news&g=912 Sorinetsport.ir]</ref>\n\n===Persepolis===\n[[File:Omid Alishah.jpg|thumb|233x233px|Alishah at [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] training.]]\nHe signed a two-year contract with [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] on 11 June 2013.<ref>{{cite web\n |title       = Official: Omid Alishah joins Persepolis\n |url         = http://www1.fc-perspolis.com/news_content/main/newsId:10971\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20130921054737/http://www1.fc-perspolis.com/news_content/main/newsId%3A10971\n |archivedate = 2013-09-21\n}}</ref> He made his debut on 16 August 2013 in a match against [[Malavan F.C.|Malavan]], in which he scored the winning goal. He scored his second goal on 6 April 2014 in a 2\u20132 draw against his former team, [[Rah Ahan F.C.|Rah Ahan]]. On 23 November 2014, Alishah scored the winning goal in the [[Tehran derby]] against rival [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] in the 78th minute. He was sent off after receiving his second yellow card seconds after his goal. \n\nIn 2015, before the 2015\u201316 season, Alishah was designated as the Persepolis' third captain.\n\nIn the winter of 2017, Alishah signed a two\u2013year contract with [[Tractor S.C.|Tractor]] to spend his conscription period at the club. Alishah returned to Persepolis Besore [[2018\u201319 Persian Gulf Pro League|2018-19]] [[Persian Gulf Cup|Pro League]].\n\n==International career==\n\n===U\u201317===\nAlishah represented [[Iran national under-17 football team|Iran U-17]] in the 3 of the 4 games the team played at the [[2009 FIFA U-17 World Cup]].<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/01/11/93/31/fu17_2009_squadlists.pdf Fifa.com]</ref>\n\n===U\u201320===\nHe also made the squad for the unsuccessful [[2010 AFC U-19 Championship]], surprisingly his involvement was highly limited under the guidance of his former U17 manager, [[Ali Doustimehr]].<ref>[http://www.varzesh3.com/news.do?itemid=27655&title=%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85_%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A_%D8%AA%D9%8A%D9%85_%D9%85%D9%84%D9%8A_%D8%AC%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86 Varzesh3.com]</ref>\n\n===U-22===\nHe was invited to [[Iran national under-23 football team|Iran U-22]] by the coach [[Alireza Mansourian]].<ref>[http://www.ffiri.ir/news/detail/\u0645\u0646\u0635\u0648\u0631\u06cc\u0627\u0646-20-\u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646-\u0631\u0627-\u062f\u0639\u0648\u062a-\u06a9\u0631\u062f/102147/news.aspx Ffiri.ir]</ref> He made his debut against [[Qatar national under-23 football team|Qatar U-22]] and scored his first goal at the match.<ref>[http://www.ffiri.ir/national-football-team/player/%D8%A7%D9%85%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B4%D8%A7%D9%87/57edca5d-ac39-40d3-85ce-b4d3d3e72838/NationalTeamUnder22/detail.aspx Ffiri.ir]</ref>\n\n===Senior===\n\nHe made his debut against [[Guam national football team|Guam]] on 3 September 2015 in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualifying]].\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===Club career statistics===\n{{updated|27 February 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Division\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Hazfi Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Asian Football Confederation|Asia]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n! Apps !! Goals !! Apps !! Goals !! Apps !! Goals !! Apps !! Goals \n|-\n|[[Nassaji Mazandaran F.C.|Nassaji]]\n|[[Azadegan League|Division 1]]\n|[[2009\u201310 Azadegan League|2009\u201310]]\n|10||1||0||0||\u2013||\u2013||10||1